```

### JavaScript (script.js)

```javascript
document.getElementById('open-chat-btn').addEventListener('click', function() {
  document.getElementById('chat-modal').style.display = 'block';
  populateChatHistory();
});

function populateChatHistory() {
  const chatHistory = document.getElementById('chat-history');
  const messages = [
    { sender: 'Human', text: 'Hello, how are you?' },
    { sender: 'AI', text: 'I am just a computer program, so I don\'t have feelings, but I\'m here to help!' },
    { sender: 'Human', text: 'That\'s cool. Do you know the weather forecast for tomorrow?' },
    { sender: 'AI', text: 'I can\'t access real-time data, but I can tell you it\'s sunny and 25°C.' },
  ];

  messages.forEach(function(message) {
    const div = document.createElement('div');
    div.innerHTML = `${message.sender}: ${message.text}`;
    chatHistory.appendChild(div);
  });
}
```

This example creates a simple modal that opens when a button is clicked, displaying a chat history with four messages: two from a human and two from an AI chatbot. The messages are dynamically added to the chat history within the modal using JavaScript, ensuring a simple interaction without the need for a backend server.

### Note:

